@node "HumMission 5"
This is a HARD mission (as reported by Simon on #Amiga} and I agree.Firstly the
oil driller will only arrive in ten minutes from NE.just South of the Command
base down a slope is an oil deposit but don't send the oil driller there just
yet.Build a solar powerplant and Refinery and send the oil tanker past an oil
deposit to the East of your base and slightly N out of harms way.If you do not
drill this site first the Robots will claim it first.Back at base make some
preparations for defence by building two cannon nests.If in general you try and
spread your base SE. down the slope towards the oil deposit nearby.At about the
five minte interval you will be attacked but don't be tempted to
build,build,build just yet! save your credits to repair your cannons.Position
your light tank and armoured vehicles in front of your cannons but not out of
their firing range.this will give them some protection.position your bazookers
so that they can protect close quarter combat with your cannons.However be aware
that the robots will destroy your soldiers if they break through.Watch out for
sneak attacks and repel them by using your light tank(it's faster!)By now you
would have realised that the enemy has some mean heavy vehicles and in fact it
has a medium factory which can be upgraded to a heavy factory.This means that
they will throw Medium tanks,Rocket launchers,Tiger tanks and laser tanks
    When your oil driller arrives save the game and send it to the oil next to
its entrance.Do not forget to send the oil tanker to the oil tower as soon as
it's built ;-/.When your first shipment of oil nears your base protect it with
any vehicle which isn't heavily damaged(common sense i know but save your
damaged vehicles by putting them towards the N of your base.Start building a
repair centre to get them repaired.Next try and build a Barracks and light
factory before you add any more cannon nests to protect them.otherwis you will
have nests not being used effectively.keep an eye on that oil tanker if you lose
it you'lll have to wait until you build a research centre and upgrade your
factory to replace it.
    when you there is "no more oil available" manufacture another oil driller
and erect your tower,you've guessed it,near your base.Make sure you send the oil
tanker to the new tower asap. Build cannon defenses next to your Oil tower and
near to prevent incursions and sneak attacks.Everything goes along
swimmingly until you run out of oil again.if an rocket launcher or laser tank
singles out a light tank it is doomed so as soon as its armour is red lined select
it and press "R" to send it to be repaired.
    By now the Robots will be fully charged and seething with rage and want that
oil tower .This is where i am up to now but wait they
have Mobile Bomber(capable of really having your eye out!) now then if only
they'd stop shooting me...Right I have played this level several times nearly
completing it only the once.For me the best way to win seems to be patience
Try and build up defences of cannon nests with a couple of rows of light tanks
surrounding them and any soldiers behind them.If you attack any enemy oil tower
the Robots retaliate in FORCE and you will have to retreat.It's best to sit back
and absorb any punishment they can dish out at your base.At all costs watch your
oil tanker if it gets damaged you may be hindered so repair it when it smokes.
    They keep on coming for your oil but if defended well enough you will almost
wipe out their heavy units.After an hour and twenty minutes or so(depending how
quick you are)You will be tempted to approach the enemy base to the South.Attack
the defense en masse.make sure you have made them form a group so you can send
them back for repair if need be quickly.Next attempt to acquire their refinery
for if you do so you can build cannon nests next to it(he says... as if it's
easy :-))and this is as far as i've got to date... Until now:)))) I have to say
on and off this has taken me 2 weeks but i have completed this mission.When
time=roughly1hr 20min you should be in a position to pester the enemy.Its base
is South of a large spaceship wreck and you will encounter resistance near oil
towers (empty aren't they) but ignore them for now.attack their defences and
regroup and or repair before advancing some more.Your next target should be the
Command base,but the Robots still have full silos and several oil towers so it
takes time but destroy it.next target the medium factory(there is a light one
also).Be aware of rocket launchers and mob them if they attack.the refinery and
silos should be captured for the booty.All should be plane sailing until the
Barracks which has a sting in it's tail.if attacked or approached in the wrong
way it unleashes a stream of foot soldiers who advance on your base(oh are my
defences ok?)
@endnode
@node "RobMission 1"
Missions 1-4 on the Robots' side are completed and will be added soon...
good news i am back and even though i lost some save games i will endeavour
to catch up and advise anyone who needs it @16/7/99 i can give you hints
towards the first 5 robot missions as follows...

this is quite an easy introductory level just send your buggee to scout and
when you spot an enemy send reinforcements and attack en masse.try to use
your flamers to take out bazookers.you should be able to get the first shot
in or even kill the bazooker before he kills you.attack jeeps with
minigunners as they are quick firing and despose of them quickly
@endnode
@node "RobMission 3"
Destroy enemy radar
there is oil to the se. and nw but they are only half full
the enemy base is to the ne.you will come across a light factory
first.further up the path to the ne.are two radar posts
@endnode
@node "RobMission 4"
Protect the convoy(arrival in twenty minutes)

there is oil to the east.after 4mins the enemy attacks from the jungle to
the nw.try to block this gap connecting the desert with the jungle.when the
area is secure send a bugee east then south along the southernmost edge to
find oil.send an oil driller and escort of two light tanks and two flamersto
ensure safe passage of the oil driller and later the oil tankers.Position
these units at the midpoint between the trees and southernmost edge of the
jungle
   When you have enough resources block the gap connecting the jungle and
the enemy base to the north.East of the enemy base is another oil patch/well
if you secure this well you can proceed North and atack the enemy from the
rear destroying another well.If you now leave units covering this patch then
the enemy throw themselves at you
   When the convoy appears to the extreme SE of the battlescape allow them
to filter into the nearby trees and then STOP! them.If not they will proceed
on course and be destroyed by cannon nests in the enemy base b4 you have had
chance to neutralise them.cannon nests require about ten lightg tanks to
destroy them efficiently.Try to capture enemy repair centre so you can use
it for your battle worn tanks.As long as your convoy is intact AND you
DESTROY the enemy base you will complete the mission
@endnode

@node "RobMission 5"
You need to capture an informant and destroy the enemy base for this one.
Your base is located to the south of the map and the humans' to the far NE.To
the West of your base is a Ramp down which the humans constantly attack.Firstly
send your oil driller East to find oil.Then build a solar plant and refinery.So
far so good.This oil tower to the east is the only one that is freely available
so you need to go hunting asap.
    Send your armour to the base of the slope and file your soldiers behind them
as soon as you can build a barracks and a technician and assign him to the group
by the slope.Now advance North until you come across an enemy oil tower to the
East.This is your target!
    If you managed to secure this tower build another oil tanker and send them
both to this tower to suck it dry.Send your group back to guard the base
When it is half empty the humans decide they want it back and attack.Now send
your group to the tower and fend them off.By this time u will need a repair
centre and to build more units.
    If you're like me one of your oil tankers would of been destroyed by now but
there is a safer passage for them..
you can either a) build two tunnels and send your tankers through them
or             b) watch the tankers like a hawk and if they get caught then move
them off to the west(in the trees) or down a twisting back way to your base to
the east.If the humans overwhelm you by the captured tower then retreat and
repair as they do not try to claim this oil very quickly.You may have noticed
another well NW of the one you captured but don't touch it ??!!
    As at 16/03/99 i have 14000 credits and have retreated to my base.I have
laid structures to the slope by my base and put three defences there.South of
them is a platoon of light tanks which,as a group,i play hit and run with the
oncoming Marauder tanks.When a marauder attacks my nests and starts to smoke i
close the door with my light tanks and pick them off one by one.If you spot a
rocket launcher attack it like a wolf pack b4 it can fire on your nest.
    Now here's the sly part;-/ You know that original oil tower you had well
build up towards it and put a defense ws02 there to partially protect it.When
the oil in the second tower is exhausted DO NOT destroy it yet if you do the
humans will flatten you to try and get it.instead empty your original
tower,destroy it and send a new oil driller to build a new tower there.after it
is empty destroy it again and wait...Soon enough the humans send an advanced
party and one of their oil drillers,but let them build uninterruptedly.Assuming
your defense is in range of the tower it will automatically fire thereby
draining the humans credits be aware that this is a lengthy process i am talking
2 and a half hours,but to attack their base now is mass suicide.
    To the west of your base build three defenses by that slope.Try and put a
group of 9 light tanks in the gaps of the trees and use the techniques mentioned
above.REPAIR any damaged units or they'll be singled out.Gradually their attacks
subside but watch for sneak attacks.the computer will let you know if the energy
is low on any structure as an insurance.When you need more oil attack that
second tower and carefully shepherd your oil tankers to and fro.If you then
destroy the tower you will bait them out so that some of their units will then
move on and throw themselves at your defenses.
    To attack their base approach and destroy a rocket nest and head north
around the base but don't consider this until the coast is clear.Firstly take
their refinery luverly 6000 credits for me:) then build a new barracks next to
it for more technicians.then take the three silos it took me up to 24k from 2k
credits.By now the humans should be penniless so take out the command base
etc...
@node "RobMission 6"
You have to send a spy to the enemy base.In actual fact it is a technician you
need to send into the enemy command base.This is proving to be a taxing mission
as you only have thirty minutes to complete this task and it just doesn't seem
long enough for me.When you start the Mission there is no near oil patch the
nearest one is around the coast to the NE so immediately send your oil driller
and rocket launchers north as they are slow moving vehicles.When you hear" new
buildings available"start the usual routine of building ie Solar pwer plant the
Refinery at the same time send a buggy ahead to scout for that oil patch.
    My tactics are that you send all initial units to the SE of the oil well you
will notice that the enemy attack you from the south so try and form a two rows
of units to block their exit.If you do not they will sweep around and attack
your unguarded base.send the bugees East of this oil to find another patch.The
Humans are trying to gain possession of it and may have already done so.if
they haven't you will need to keep sending units South of the second patch to
guard it until it is needed.Incidentally this is the only other exit the Humans
have from their base.Eventually you can build a medium factory which will allow
you to build medium tanks and rocket launchers.Remember to dismantle units which
are weaker and replace them with harder options.Build two more oil tankers to
speed up the production rate.When you hear "no more oil available from the first
tower send your tankers to the location of the second.ENSURE that your line of
defence SE of that first tower is forcing your tankers to pass behind it ie send
it south a bit if it is not.
    Now you need to keep amassing forces south of the second tower and advance
South eventually your forces will come into range of the human cannon
nests.there are three of them just west of them is the Radar and command base
the command base is guarded by another cannon and lots of heavier units swarm at
you I am sure someone has finished this level if they have any better tactics
please feel free to spill the beans.If you manage to weaken the command base
enough send in a technician (good luck)
@endnode
@node "RobMission 7"
destroy the human's research center.
There is oil available to the West and further away to the NE of your mobile
CV.The enemy base is NW up a path which swings East and finally North until
it reaches the Mid entrance to the base.Try to carefully ammass forces on
this path and move them quickly towards the enemy base.The laser tank is a
fast firing beast and appears to have slightly more range than the Tiger
tank and has more armour so it may be best positioned nearer to the enemy than the tiger to
catch them with a volley sooner.The enemy research is well defended by a
rocket nest and a few canon nests which will need removing before you can
enter the center.position a wall of forces stopping any enemy coming out
of their base from the south,there is another exit to the East but the heavy 
factory is nearer to the southern one.Build a tunnel just nearby.Importanly
because of the distances covered in getting to the enemy research center you
will need a transporter to carry a couple of saboteurs to destroy it.To ake saboteurs you will need to upgrade the barracks twice.
   Block off the way towards the eastern entrance of the human's base
and start to send forces north.You will come across two oil towers,but their
oil is depleted so pass them by if possible.There is a rocket nest up here
and can easily be taken out by positioning a couple to the top right
   to head towards the research center you will need to enter the base and turn south then east past the entrance to their heavy factory.here you
will encounter harsh resistance so be prepared!further to the west are silos
and the center itself

@endnode
@node "RobMission 8"
In this mission you are required to destroy everything and this is where
things start to get a little tricky.Obviously you will need to make room and
send your oil driller west until you find oil.Just South of this oil is a
way into your base,which is used by the humans and must be blocked off.There
are three main ways into your base from which the humans attack,but start
with the southern one.try and build towards this gap and block it off with
say a heavy fatory and a nuclear power plant.Obviously you will need to have
a couple of rows of friendlies paving the way infront of your
structures.then put up four staggered defenses.In my strategy this
completely seals off access to my base for both sides,but you could always
put a lone unit in place of one defense but run the risk of it moving or
being compromised.The next plan is to search ahead for more oil and this can
be found to the East of your base and then south.if you send a couple of
bugees and lght tanks you will come across three oil patches; the first is
half full the second three-quarters full and the third is full so head for
that one and build there first if you can.Keep sending forces to this
position to watch over your supply lines.WARNING!!! you will come under
heavy fire so send lots of armour here!You will essentially need a tunnel
behind your units at this location due to the long distance back to be
repaired.
   For the gap to the west i sent many forces here,destroyed the first
well and built a tunnel there.then i sent a mobile cv to the site to block off 
gap with a new comm.center with two defenses in front of it(Again
completely sealed off.Now unless your lines are breached the only way in and
out of your base is using tunnels,or the entrance by the three oil deposits
to the east.I chose not not seal off this part....
   As long as you keep refreshing your frontline units try and move
south from that western approach .laser tanks are very useful here as there
is a special factory nearby throwing out sioux helicopters so put them on
the front row.Don't forget to send saboteurs to take out buildings which are
difficult to destroy.
   The enemy base is situated in the se corner of the map and you will
need to negotiate several canon/rocket nests.If you take out the power
plants,in theory,enemy rejuvenation should slow down.When attacks towards
the three oil wells cease then move those forces west to attack human defenses and take out the silos
@endnode
@node "RobMission 9"
You have to destroy the enemy oil towers,BUT,not all of them!If you find the
pyramid on the surface of the desert there are five oil wells south of it
and one to the east of it which need destroying to win.I find the best way
is to send a transporter with saboteurs to the well,destroy it and then
claim the remaining oil with an oil driller.
   When you begin there is oil to the immediate south.but also send
units to the east to guard another oil patch.Laser tanks seem to have a
problem in targetting sioux from below so if the 'copter is south of a
building send the tank north of it and then it can fire.Between the oil to
the east and your base is a path south with a full well.This well is one of
the six you need to complete the mission and that direction is the one to
follow to the other 4 to the south of the pyramid.
   The humans have a habit of sneaking into your base by copter from
the north and past the pyramid through the trees.I placed two ws01 defenses
between the trees and the pyramid and a couple of tiger tanks and rocket
launcher behind them.When you can build an antigrav factory construct about
9 antigrav an use them to ambush oil tankers.Watch out for rocket launchers
though.
@endnode
