Ha ha this is what we've been playing for.These are awesome but slow and need
protection.They can single handedly destroy buildings but there destruction can
affect close allies especially soldiers.These launchers are more suited to long
range shots and seem to be able to fire as far as rocket launchers
@endnode
@node "Sioux"
Vulnerable towards rocket launchers and defence WS02.They are fairly fast and
only safe against antigrav if in groups of 4-6.Their strength lies in speed and
destructiveness.
@endnode
@node "WS01"
These can annihilate your forces.You can atack them from N,E,S,W but not always
successfully. it is best that a half dozen helicopters take them out quickly and
without damage.They are very destructive but dangerous to your friends and
family.You will need to position them on the outskirts of your bases
perimeter,as they damage or destroy anything in their beam and will do more
harm than good in between buildings.Two side by side can destroy
rocket launchers and medium tanks with one shot but not always.There is a
mistake in the manual despite what it says ws01 cannot fire on aircraft
If you place a ws01 too close to buildings when it discharges it takes
damage
@endnode
@node "CAPTURE"
To capture enemy buildings...
1)Send a formidable force including engineers or technicians close to the
entrance of the structure(if possible).Flamers/grenadiers/bazookers all cause a
lot of damage to buildings but are vulnerable to attack especially wehn moving
to the front line.
2)Arrange your force so that the NW in close proximity to the required structure
is clear and place a technician or engineer there.Otherwise your units may kill
him with friendly fire.
3)Attack the structure until its energy bar is in the red then send your man in
as close to the structure as possible with the animated cursor.
4)if the structure is not repaired send your man into the structure when you
have the two green cursor arrows showing over it."building captured"
@endnode
@node "AUTOMAN"
As far as i am aware you cannot automatically produce new units from the
barracks or factories,However you can order a certain amount to be built one
after the other.For starters make sure you have enough power.Then click on the
unit you want to produce.then hit the RMB the number of units less one you want
to produce.
@endnode
@node "triple tanks"
triple tanks have greater velocity than ion launchers and are therefore
quicker to attack and move to far off places so prefer them to ion
launchers when sending out heavy scouting parties
@endnode
@node "antiantigrav"
have you ever noticed that when enemy forces approach your bases sometimes
they halt and an antigrav hovers over the top of them?well if the antigrav
is shot down it drops vertically onto any unit below it causing severe or
critical damage to that unit
@endnode
@node "napalm strike"
this is particularly effective.I managed to destroy a heavy factory with
this as the plane makes three passes over its target and is very accurate
@endnode

